# M6 — CTF mid-round respawn flow.
#
# Verifies the user-reported bug fix: in CTF, killing a player must NOT
# end the round; the dead mech respawns after RESPAWN_DELAY_TICKS (180
# ticks = 3 s at 60 Hz) and play continues. Round-end is gated on
# capture-score / time-limit only.
#
# Local mech (mech_id 0, team RED) gets killed by kill_peer at tick 30.
# After the 3-second respawn delay it should be alive again at a fresh
# RED spawn. Match phase must stay ACTIVE the whole time — CTF skips
# the solo_warning rule entirely so the round doesn't end on first kill.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/m5_ctf_respawn
seed 1 2

map crossfire
mode ctf

# Park the player on a known platform so the pre-kill frame is stable.
spawn_at 600 950

contact_sheet ctf_respawn cols 4 cell 320 180

# Tick 1: pristine spawn — full HP, alive.
at 1   shot t01_alive_pre_kill

# Tick 30: kill the local mech via direct mech_kill. Carrier state is
# irrelevant — we just need the death to arm respawn_at_tick. The next
# tick the mech is in ragdoll free-fall.
at 30 kill_peer 0
at 35  shot t35_just_killed
at 90  shot t90_dead_ragdoll

# RESPAWN_DELAY_TICKS = 180; arm tick = 30, so respawn lands at tick
# 210. Match phase should still be MATCH_PHASE_ACTIVE — no round-end.
at 200 shot t200_pre_respawn
at 215 shot t215_post_respawn_alive
at 240 shot t240_settled_after_respawn

# Keep playing past where solo_warning would normally have triggered
# (3 s after the kill = tick 210; pre-fix the round would have ended
# at or before this point). 350 well past it.
at 350 shot t350_round_still_active

at 360 end
